pdftex.map has
  ptmro8r ".167 SlantFont TeXBase1Encoding ReEncodeFont" <8r.enc <utmr8a.pfb

The PS-Name in the map-file is omitted to work around a bug in pdftex.
Thus, pdftex.map is not a valid map file for dvips (and it was never
ment to be used with dvips).

So, I repeat myself: teTeX-beta users should use the switches
  -Poutline / -Ppk / -Pdownload35 / -Pbuildin35
to control which level of type1 fonts to use / download.

  -u +pdftex.map
should never be used for dvips.

Thomas

